cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about object detection and segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a deep learning architecture for this task, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a structured loss function, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of recursive neural networks (ReNNs) is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to guide the region grouping process, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
